<head2>(Changing the Clock Display\settings)
<p>
 You can customize the clock display to include any
 combination of the date and time regions. To change
 the clock display, choose Settings... from the Options
 menu. A dialog box appears.
<p>
  If the check button for Analog, Digital, or Date
 is highlighted, Clock displays the time or date in that format.
 If the check button for 24 Hour Digital
 Time is highlighted, Clock displays the 
 time using a 24-hour digital format.
<p>
Click MB1 on a highlighted check button to turn
the display off, or click on a check button that is
not highlighted to turn the display on.
<p>
 To save your new clock settings, click on OK.
To cancel your changes, click on Cancel.

<P>
