<head2>(Setting the Alarm\setting_alarm)
<p>
 You can use the alarm to remind you of appointments. 
<p>
To set the alarm:
<list>(numbered)
<le>Choose Settings... from the Options menu or
 click MB3 anywhere in the window.  You see the Settings dialog box.
<le>Click on the Alarm check button to switch the
 alarm on. The alarm is on if the check button is highlighted.
<le>Click on the left-hand Alarm Settings entry box.  Enter the hour (in 
either standard or military format) at which you want the alarm to activate.  
Then, click on the right-hand Alarm Settings entry box and enter the 
minutes.
<p>
If you set the hour and minutes in standard format, click on the AM or PM 
radio button.  For military (1300 hours to 2400 hours) format, Clock 
sets the time of day.
<le>When you set the alarm, an alarm bell appears in the Clock window to 
indicate that the alarm is set.  When the alarm sounds, the message appears 
in a pop-up window.
<le>Click on the Alarm Message entry box.  Enter the alarm message you want 
to display.  The alarm message can contain up to 200 characters.
<le>Click on OK to save your settings, or click on Cancel to cancel your 
changes.
<endlist>


<P>
