<head4>(Settings...\set_menu)
<p>                          
 To change the Clock display, choose Settings... from the Options
 menu. Or, double click MB1 anywhere in the window (except in the menu bar 
and the title bar).  
<p>
You see the Clock Settings dialog box.
<p>
To change the Clock settings:
<list>(numbered)
<le>
Click MB1 on a highlighted check button to turn a display off.
Or, click MB1 on a check button that is
not highlighted to turn a display on.
<le>If the Alarm check button is highlighted (which indicates
that you want the 
alarm bell to sound):
<list>(alphabetic)
<le>Click 
MB1 on the left-hand Alarm Settings 
entry box.  Enter the hour (in either standard or military format) at which
you want the alarm to sound.
Then, click MB1 on the right-hand Alarm Settings entry box and enter the 
minutes.  
<p>
If you set the hour and minutes in standard format, click MB1 on the AM or 
PM radio button.
For military format (1300 hours to 2400 hours), 
Clock sets the time of day.
<p>
When you set the alarm, an alarm bell appears in the Clock window to
indicate that the alarm is set.  When the alarm sounds, Clock displays
the message in a pop-up window.
<le>Click MB1 on the Alarm Message entry box.  Enter the alarm
message you want to display.  The alarm message can contain up to 200
characters. 
<endlist>
<le>To save your new Clock settings, click on OK.
<le>To cancel your changes, click on Cancel.
<endlist>

<P>
