<p>
Clock displays the date, including the name of the month, the
day of the month, and
the day of the week.

<p>
To display the date, click on the Date check button in the Settings dialog
box.

  
<head2>(Military Clock\military_clk)
<p>
Clock displays military time (24-hour time system) as it would appear on a
24-hour clock.

<p>
To display the time in military format, click on the 24 Hour Digital Time 
check
in the Settings dialog box.
  
<head2>(Options Menu\clk_optmenu)
<p>
The Options menu includes the following menu items:
<list>(Unnumbered\-)
<le> Settings...
<le> Save Settings
<le> Restore System Settings
<le> Help
<le> Exit
<endlist>


<head2>(OK Button\ok_button)           
<p>
To confirm changes you make
to the Clock default settings, click on OK.

<P>
Additional topics:
